@group orders
@endpoint POST /orders
@desc Create order
@required {OrderReference: str, TotalPrice: num(double), Restaurant: any, Customer: map{Name!: str, Email: str, PhoneNumber!: str, DisplayPhoneNumber: str, Address!: map{Lines!: [str], City!: str, PostalCode!: str, GeoLocation: map}}, Fulfilment: map{Method!: str, DueDate!: str(date-time), DueAsap: bool}, Payment: map{PaidDate: str(date-time), Tips: [map{Value: num(money), Type: str}], Fees: [map{Value: num(money), Type: str}], Taxes: [map{Value!: num(money), Type!: str, Percentage!: num(double)}], Lines!: [map{Type!: str, Value: num(money), Paid: bool, LastCardDigits: str, ServiceFee: num(double)}]}, Items: [map{TotalPrice!: num(money), Reference!: str, Name!: str, Quantity!: int, UnitPrice: int(money), Items: [map{Reference: str, Name: str, Quantity: int, UnitPrice: int(money), Items: [map]}]}]}
@optional {x-je-api-version: num=1 # The api version to use. Version 2.0 is the only available version., FriendlyOrderReference: str, CustomerNotes: map{NoteForRestaurant: str, NoteForDelivery: str}, IsTest: bool}
@returns(201) {OrderId: str} # Created
@errors {400: Bad Request - Request is for deprecated API version or has failed validation in some way - see response body for details, 409: Conflict - you've already told us about an order with this `OrderReference`}

@endgroup

@group order-ready-for-preparation-async
@endpoint POST /order-ready-for-preparation-async
@desc Order ready for preparation (async)
@optional {OrderId: str, Currency: str, TotalPrice: num(money), Fulfilment: map{Method: str, CustomerDueDate: str(date-time), CustomerDueAsap: bool, PrepareFor: str(date-time), PreparationTime: str(timespan), Address: map{Lines: [str], City: str, PostalCode: str, Geolocation: map}, PhoneNumber: str}, Payment: map{Lines: [map{Type: str, Value: num(money), Paid: bool}]}, Customer: map{Id: str, Name: str}, Items: [map{Reference: str, Name: str, Quantity: int, UnitPrice: int(money), Items: [map{Reference: str, Name: str, Quantity: int, UnitPrice: int(money), Items: [map]}]}], PriceBreakdown: map{Discount: num(money), Tips: num(money), Taxes: num(money), Items: num(money), Fees: map{Delivery: num(money), ServiceCharge: num(money), Other: num(money)}}, CustomerNotes: map, PlacedDate: str(date-time), Restaurant: map{Id: str, Reference: str, Name: str, Address: map{Lines: [str], City: str, PostalCode: str, Geolocation: map}, PhoneNumber: str}, IsTest: bool}
@returns(202) Upon successful receipt of this event, a `202` status code should be returned, indicating the request has been accepted. You should then later respond with the result of processing this request, via the [callback URL](#section/Async-Webhooks) endpoint.
@errors {400: Should the initial validation of the order fail, return a `400` status code. NOTE: In this instance we do not also expect a failure callback via the async callback URL.}

@endgroup

@group order-ready-for-preparation-sync
@endpoint POST /order-ready-for-preparation-sync
@desc Order ready for preparation (sync)
@optional {OrderId: str, Currency: str, TotalPrice: num(money), Fulfilment: map{Method: str, CustomerDueDate: str(date-time), CustomerDueAsap: bool, PrepareFor: str(date-time), PreparationTime: str(timespan), Address: map{Lines: [str], City: str, PostalCode: str, Geolocation: map}, PhoneNumber: str}, Payment: map{Lines: [map{Type: str, Value: num(money), Paid: bool}]}, Customer: map{Id: str, Name: str}, Items: [map{Reference: str, Name: str, Quantity: int, UnitPrice: int(money), Items: [map{Reference: str, Name: str, Quantity: int, UnitPrice: int(money), Items: [map]}]}], PriceBreakdown: map{Discount: num(money), Tips: num(money), Taxes: num(money), Items: num(money), Fees: map{Delivery: num(money), ServiceCharge: num(money), Other: num(money)}}, CustomerNotes: map, PlacedDate: str(date-time), Restaurant: map{Id: str, Reference: str, Name: str, Address: map{Lines: [str], City: str, PostalCode: str, Geolocation: map}, PhoneNumber: str}, IsTest: bool}
@returns(200) Respond with a 200 status code to indicate that you have received the notification.

@endgroup

